<materialsCitation id="3B303C9AFFBF935155CDA20FFA56F980" collectionCode="FISH" collectorName="S Hind" county="Silver" elevation="20" latitude="11.12" location="The" municipality="Sete de Setembro River" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" specimenCount="1">
<location id="8E87601CFFBF935155CDA20FFF05F9E0" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03F187D1FFBD93515642A12CFA52F980:8E87601CFFBF935155CDA20FFF05F9E0" box="[166,208,1557,1576]" county="Silver" latitude="11.12" municipality="Sete de Setembro River" name="The" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">The</location>
specimens collected from the tributaries of the 
<collectingMunicipality id="6B83ACBDFFBF935157BEA20FFE93F980" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Sete de Setembro River</collectingMunicipality>
had 2n = 42 chromosomes (
<quantity id="4CA09B22FFBF93515707A22FFD77F980" box="[620,674,1589,1608]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" unit="m" value="20.0">
<elevation id="0075D1F4FFBF93515707A22FFD77F980" box="[620,674,1589,1608]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" unit="m" value="20.0">20 m</elevation>
</quantity>
+ 22 sm) and FN = 84 for both males and females, with no heteromorphic sex chromosome system. C-banding revealed pericentromeric bands in nearly all the chromosomes as well as small terminal bands on some pairs. 
<collectingCounty id="62864E4BFFBF93515418A2AFFE66F900" box="[371,435,1717,1736]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Silver</collectingCounty>
nitrate staining revealed three chromosome pairs (
<geoCoordinate id="EE6C5000FFBF93515420A2CFFE56F920" box="[331,387,1749,1768]" degrees="4, 9" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" precision="5555" value="4.9">n 4, 9</geoCoordinate>
and 15) withAg-NORs (
<figureCitation id="13632A42FFBF935157EAA2CFFD23F920" box="[641,758,1749,1768]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[136,175,1877,1896]" captionTargetBox="[223,1343,636,1821]" captionTargetId="figure-276@2.[204,1376,614,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with conventional Giemsa staining (a, d, g) and C-banding (b, e, h) of the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b), Araguaia (d, e) and Xingu (g, h) Rivers. Boxes display chromosomes with Ag-NORs in the populations from the São Francisco (c), Araguaia (f) and Xingu (i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421617" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421617/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CA09B22FFBF935157C4A2CFFD1EF920" box="[687,715,1749,1768]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
, h, i
</figureCitation>
). 
<collectionCode id="ED49AE02FFBF935155EAA2EFFF6EF8C0" box="[129,187,1781,1800]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">FISH</collectionCode>
with the 5S rDNA probe revealed only one metacentric pair (n 8) labeled in the interstitial region of the long arms (
<figureCitation id="13632A42FFBF935155E2A32FFF02F880" box="[137,215,1845,1864]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[129,168,1387,1406]" captionTargetBox="[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-352@3.[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) using 5S rDNA (a, d, g), 18S rDNA (b, e, h) and 5SHindIII satellite DNA (c, f, i) probes in the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b, c), Araguaia (d, e, f) and Xingu (g, h, i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421619/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CA09B22FFBF935155D2A32FFF02F880" box="[185,215,1845,1864]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" unit="g" value="2.0">2g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). 18S rDNA sites were labeled in the terminal region of the long arms in three pairs of chromosomes: two metacentric pairs (n 4 and 9) and one submetacentric pair (n 15) (
<figureCitation id="13632A42FFBF935155D8A38FFED1F860" box="[179,260,1941,1960]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[129,168,1387,1406]" captionTargetBox="[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetId="figure-352@3.[129,1452,174,1370]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Hoplias malabaricus karyotypes (karyomorph A) with fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH) using 5S rDNA (a, d, g), 18S rDNA (b, e, h) and 5SHindIII satellite DNA (c, f, i) probes in the populations from the basins of the São Francisco (a, b, c), Araguaia (d, e, f) and Xingu (g, h, i) Rivers. Scale bar = 5μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5421619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5421619/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2h</figureCitation>
). 
<collectionCode id="ED49AE02FFBF9351547CA38FFE84F860" box="[279,337,1941,1960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">FISH</collectionCode>
with the 5 
<collectorName id="26AD5311FFBF935154A8A38FFDDDF860" box="[451,520,1941,1960]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">
S 
<emphasis id="B92CEAD5FFBF935154B9A38FFDDDF860" box="[466,520,1941,1960]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Hind</emphasis>
</collectorName>
III satellite DNA probe identified 10 chromosome pairs with sites in the centromeric region: four metacentric pairs (
<geoCoordinate id="EE6C5000FFBF935151E0A20FFB07F9E0" box="[1163,1234,1557,1576]" degrees="1, 5" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" precision="5555" value="1.5">n 1, 5</geoCoordinate>
